The paper deals with the Densest k-Subgraph problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and optimization. The problem is related to various areas of computer science, including algorithms and complexity (cs.DS, cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper presents a new hardness result for the problem based on the exponential time hypothesis (ETH), which is a central conjecture in computational complexity theory. This makes cs.DS and cs.CC the most likely categories, followed by cs.CG, cs.IT, and cs.LG.
